Alstom, BNP Paribas, NRJ Group, Recyclex: French Stock Preview

-- B y   J a m e s   H e r t l i n g   a n d   S t e p h e n   T a y l o r
-- 
2011-05-04T04:01:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-03/alstom-bnp-paribas-nrj-group-french-stock-preview-correct-.html
The following is a list of companies
whose stocks may have unusual changes in Paris. Symbols are in
parentheses after company names and prices are from the last
close.  France ’s CAC 40 Index fell 11.93 or 0.3 percent, to
4,096.84 in Paris. The SBF 120 Index fell 0.3 percent to
3,071.51.  Groupe Flo (FLO FP): The restaurateur said it was
“cautious” on the 2011 outlook after reporting first-quarter
net income rose to 3.1 million euros from 2.1 million euros. The
shares rose 1.4 percent to 7.24 euros.  Hermes International (RMS)  : The luxury-goods maker
booked a 30 million-euro profit from the sale of a stake in Jean
Paul Gaultier to  Spain ’s Puig. Hermes fell 0.5 percent to 158.85
euros.  NRJ Group (NRG)  : The media company said first-quarter
revenue rose to 83.8 million euros from 75.4 million euros. The
shares fell 8 cents to 8.11 euros.  Osiatis SA (OSA)  : The computer-services company said
first-quarter revenue rose 12 percent to 67.1 million euros.
Shares were unchanged at 6.00 euros.  Recyclex SA (RX FP): The metals company said first-quarter
sales fell to 98.6 million euros from 123.4 million euros. The
shares fell 1.3 percent to 7.11 euros.  Alstom SA (ALO)  ,  BNP Paribas (BNP)  SA and  Scor SE (SCR) 
 are scheduled to report results.  To contact the reporters on this story:
